  <div class="row">
    <div class="column medium-12">
      <div class="content">
        <h2>Offsets</h2>
        <p>Offsets allow you to create additional space between columns in a row. They're nestable like the rest of the grid. You can use classes like <code>.medium-offset-1</code>, <code>.large-offset-5</code>, <code>.x-large-offset-10</code> and <code>.small-offset-3</code> to manipulate your column positions in different ways. You can offset up to 11 since you wouldn't ever offset a full-width column.</p>
        <h4>classes:</h4>
        <p><code>.small-offset-#</code> : push the div to the left at the small size</p>
        <p><code>.medium-offset-#</code> : push the div to the left at the medium size (inherit value from <code>small</code> if not defined)</p>
        <p><code>.large-offset-#</code> : push the div to the left at the large size (inherit value from <code>medium</code> if not defined)</p>
        <p><code>.x-large-offset-#</code> : push the div to the left at the x-large size (inherit value from <code>large</code> if not defined)</p>
        <h4>example:</h4>
    <pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;div class="medium-1 columns"&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="medium-11 columns"&gt;11&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;div class="medium-1 columns"&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="medium-10 medium-offset-1 columns"&gt;10, offset 1&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;div class="medium-1 columns"&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="medium-9 medium-offset-2 columns"&gt;9, offset 2&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;div class="medium-1 columns"&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="medium-8 medium-offset-3 columns"&gt;8, offset 3&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
    </pre>
      </div>
